Slow Cooker Quinoa, Sweet Potato, and Corn Casserole
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 lb sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into 1/2" pieces
2 shallots, minced
4 teaspoons chili powder
3 garlic cloves, minced
2 tsp minced fresh oregano or 1/2 tsp dried
1 tsp canola oil
2 c vegetable broth
1 c prewashed quinoa
2 red bell peppers, stemmed, seeded, and cut into 1/2" pieces
Salt and pepper
1 c frozen corn, thawed
1 avocado, halved, pitted, and cut into 1/2" pieces
2 tbsp minced fresh cilantro
lime wedges

Lightly spray inside of slow cooker with vegetable oil spray. Microwave potatoes, shallots, chili powder, garlic, oregano, and oil in covered bowl, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are softened, 6-8 min; transfer to slow cooker. Stir in broth, quinoa, bell peppers, and 1 tsp salt. Cover and cook until potatoes and quinoa are tender, 3-4 hr on low or 2-3 hr on high.
